The paper deals with negotiation between autonomous agents, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of time constraints and uncertainty in the model suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The study of equilibria and optimal outcomes also suggests the involvement of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and social choice theory (cs.SI).
